Recommend If: Someone who likes scifi and wants to try fantasy?
Thoughts: Very detailed scifi-fantasy, enjoyable story. Read due to upcoming movie I think

Name: Why the West Rules-for Now
Author: Ian Morris
Recommend If: Interested in global agenda, future of society etc
Thoughts: Good, ties in with Sapiens/Homo deus and Guns Germs and Steel. Quite loosely written, but makes the interesting case that East/West will become irrelevant and that global coordination more important to avoid global chaos due to food security, migration etc

Name: Animal Farm
Author: George Orwell
Thoughts: Reread in 2020 (the Ukranian? version, with great intro by George Orwell) , very good, enjoyed reading about UK/RUS relations and how/why this was written

Name: The Last Grain Race
Author: Eric Newby
Thoughts: Very accurate representation of sailing on large boats, great detail and very relatable to Creole sailing.

Name: English Passengers
Author: Matthew Kneale
Thoughts: Hilarious and very sad, very accurate(?) representation of the colonial mindset and oppression of indigenous population wrapped into a very funny story about sailing and history

Name: How Democracies Die
Author: Steven Levitsky
Recommend If: interested in election politics and failing states
Thoughts: Excellent book on how fragile democratic systems can be and the history of the US elections

Name: The Long Walk to Freedom
Author: Nelson Mandela
Thoughts: Must read for all South Africans, loved reading this, sad to only have read it now. Excellent intro to South African near history.

Name: Utopia Avenue
Author: David Mitchell
Recommend If: Fan of David Mitchell? Probably better books but enjoyable.
Thoughts: Surprisingly enjoyed this entirely through, very familiar places in London/England. Lot of drugs
